cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with Radio Resource Management (RRM) techniques in cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of advanced user association strategies and access control mechanisms, which are related to information theory and security, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also likely categories. The paper evaluates the downlink performance of a two-tier heterogeneous network, which involves the use of multiple base station types, and introduces a modified SINR association strategy for load balancing. This makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia) also possible categories.
